1:
Yahweh, my heart is not proud or my eyes haughty.
\q I do not have great hopes for myself
\q or concern myself with things that are beyond me.
2:
Indeed I have stilled and quieted my soul;
\q like a weaned child with his mother,
\q my soul within me is like a weaned child.
\q
3:
Israel, hope in Yahweh
\q now and forever.
131:
\m
\d A song of ascents; of David.
\q
